e of the most revered of all contemporary directors, Egoyan’s forays into installation art and opera have provided evidence of his versatility and confirmed his talents. Image and Territory: Essays on Atom Egoyan is both scholarly and accessible. Indispensable for the scholar, student, and fan, this collection of new essays and interviews from leading film and media scholars unpacks the central arguments, tensions, and paradoxes of his work and traces their evolution. It also locates his work within larger intellectual and artistic currents in order to consider how he takes up and answers critical debates in politics, philosophy, and aesthetics. Most importantly, it addresses how his work is both intellectually engaging and emotionally moving.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aFilm & Media. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aArmatage, Kay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaronian, Marie-Aude, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeard, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoyd, Melanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurwell, Jennifer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurwell, Jennifer, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aClark, Caryl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGilders, Adam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGruben, Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHogikyan, Nellie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJoosse, Angela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKegel, Katrin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.